# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in the auth you use. You need ONE of the
# options below. Do NOT commit real secrets.

# Option A — run on your Claude subscription (no API key), self-hosted single
# operator. This is the default when no provider flag is given. Create the
# token with `claude setup-token` and paste it here.
# (Copy the printed sk-ant-oat01-... value; do not use $(claude setup-token).)
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=sk-ant-oat01-...

# Option B — Anthropic metered API billing (scale, concurrency, or hosting for
# others). Also powers `--anthropic`, which runs the sandboxed agent on the
# OpenHands engine with a Claude model.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# Optional model override for `--anthropic` (default: the config model):
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-5

# Option C — run the whole session on Google Gemini with `--gemini`. This one
# key powers both the planner/distiller/tutorial passes and the sandboxed agent
# (via the OpenHands engine). Install the extra: pip install 'readme2demo[gemini]'.
# GEMINI_API_KEY=...
# No Gemini model name is built into readme2demo (Google retires old ones with
# a hard 404). Name it per run (`--gemini <model>`) or set it once here:
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-3.5-flash

# Option D — run the whole session on OpenAI with `--openai`. Same shape as
# Gemini: one key for the passes and the OpenHands agent, no built-in model
# name. Install the extra: pip install 'readme2demo[openai]'.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5.1

# Optional — only for the experimental OpenHands engine (--engine openhands).
# The provider presets (--gemini / --openai / --anthropic) fill these in from
# the provider's key automatically; set them by hand only to point OpenHands
# at a different litellm model/provider.
# LLM_API_KEY=...
# LLM_MODEL=...
